00:22:06,091 --> 00:22:08,131
And those would happen about every 15 minutes or so.

463
00:22:09,686 --> 00:22:10,747
So, excuse me.

464
00:22:10,747 --> 00:22:14,791
So this is kind of like what the cadence looked like

465
00:22:14,791 --> 00:22:15,812
for a typical Telltale episode.

466
00:22:15,812 --> 00:22:18,475
And every 15 minutes worked for that format

467
00:22:18,475 --> 00:22:21,018
because we knew people were probably sitting on their couch.

468
00:22:21,018 --> 00:22:24,021
They were pretty dedicated to trying to finish the episode.

469
00:22:24,021 --> 00:22:27,104
We weren't competing for their attention as much.

470
00:22:27,962 --> 00:22:35,145
With Potter, we have these things called time-limited side quests, and those tend to be for one

471
00:22:35,145 --> 00:22:39,427
big theme that is chopped into maybe six to eight chapters, and each chapter takes place

472
00:22:39,427 --> 00:22:42,248
in a location, and they're about 10 minutes each.

473
00:22:42,248 --> 00:22:44,048
So it's a smaller time slice.

474
00:22:44,709 --> 00:22:46,009
And each chapter is a mini cliffhanger

475
00:22:46,009 --> 00:22:46,990
about halfway through.

476
00:22:46,990 --> 00:22:48,631
And that mini cliffhanger tends to come

477
00:22:48,631 --> 00:22:50,553
in the form of a question.

478
00:22:50,553 --> 00:22:52,914
It's usually they're trying to do,

479
00:22:52,914 --> 00:22:55,396
solve some mystery or figure out ingredients

480
00:22:55,396 --> 00:22:57,117
for a potion or something like that.

481
00:22:57,117 --> 00:23:00,059
So it's like a what is question,

482
00:23:00,059 --> 00:23:00,720
like what is ingredient X?

483
00:23:00,720 --> 00:23:02,301
And then they go and they work on it.

484
00:23:02,301 --> 00:23:05,423
And this is where the player spends their energy.

485
00:23:05,423 --> 00:23:08,505
And that always ends with a payoff,

486
00:23:08,505 --> 00:23:11,608
which is the, okay, now we know, we figured it out.

487
00:23:12,192 --> 00:23:17,234
and that pivots the scene to what's next.

488
00:23:17,234 --> 00:23:18,874
And each chapter usually has a choice

489
00:23:18,874 --> 00:23:20,775
and it's often a role play choice.

490
00:23:20,775 --> 00:23:24,417
So you get at least one moment of forming a relationship

491
00:23:24,417 --> 00:23:25,817
or changing a relationship with a character

492
00:23:25,817 --> 00:23:27,778
and then it ends with a hint of what's next.

493
00:23:27,778 --> 00:23:31,240
So in some senses, it is kind of like a mini version

494
00:23:31,240 --> 00:23:32,720
of the Telltale Cadence

495
00:23:32,720 --> 00:23:35,842
or like most dramatic episodic format.

496
00:23:35,842 --> 00:23:39,643
So kind of looks like this.

