00:36:16,517 --> 00:36:17,597
backwards to make this work.

757
00:36:17,597 --> 00:36:21,178
So the first frame, your boss is asking you out to dinner.

758
00:36:21,178 --> 00:36:22,078
Like, so far, so good.

759
00:36:22,078 --> 00:36:23,499
Relationships are clear.

760
00:36:23,499 --> 00:36:25,339
Stakes are clear.

761
00:36:25,339 --> 00:36:28,640
Then you notice that the game itself has to introduce a

762
00:36:28,640 --> 00:36:30,720
piece of meta text to actually tell you what

763
00:36:30,720 --> 00:36:32,601
this choice is about.

764
00:36:32,601 --> 00:36:33,801
And it's not really about.

765
00:36:35,061 --> 00:36:40,062
your love life, it's like you need access to your new boss.

766
00:36:40,062 --> 00:36:42,583
And then that's followed by,

767
00:36:42,583 --> 00:36:45,864
okay, now do you want to buy that access?

768
00:36:45,864 --> 00:36:48,764
The implication is you're gonna miss something if you don't.

769
00:36:48,764 --> 00:36:49,704
And so that's different,

770
00:36:49,704 --> 00:36:51,845
and it just works in a different part of the brain.

771
00:36:51,845 --> 00:36:57,046
And be conscious of when you mix them together,

772
00:36:57,046 --> 00:36:59,927
sometimes the gears can grind, sometimes it can work,

773
00:36:59,927 --> 00:37:02,507
but I just wanna throw that out there.

774
00:37:05,685 --> 00:37:08,525
So finally, sharing is caring.

775
00:37:08,525 --> 00:37:12,666
And when I mentioned participatory art earlier,

776
00:37:12,666 --> 00:37:15,727
I was talking about characters and dialogue

777
00:37:15,727 --> 00:37:17,228
that lend themselves to sharing.

778
00:37:17,228 --> 00:37:21,769
And what I mean by that is fan art and memes and cosplay.

779
00:37:21,769 --> 00:37:24,509
And these are a big part of games now.

780
00:37:24,509 --> 00:37:28,370
And fostering that community is really important too.

781
00:37:30,862 --> 00:37:35,825
you want to give people something that survives really well outside of the game.

782
00:37:35,825 --> 00:37:41,208
Like, are your characters too visually complex to make any sense to somebody who hasn't played them?

783
00:37:41,208 --> 00:37:46,531
Or do you have like a cool, you know, a catchphrase that like totally works outside of the game?

784
00:37:46,531 --> 00:37:49,793
If someone took a snapshot of it and sent it to their friend who never played it...

785
00:37:50,333 --> 00:37:52,554
how well would that person kind of understand

786
00:37:52,554 --> 00:37:54,175
what this game was getting at,

787
00:37:54,175 --> 00:37:57,657
either in terms of humor and tone

788
00:37:57,657 --> 00:37:59,198
or just some funny concept.

789
00:37:59,198 --> 00:38:02,319
It's absolutely worth thinking about at a very early stage

790
00:38:02,319 --> 00:38:05,881
so that you can create something shareable.

791
00:38:05,881 --> 00:38:07,962
One example of this is like

792
00:38:07,962 --> 00:38:10,984
using really distinct costume or visual designs,

793
00:38:10,984 --> 00:38:13,445
something that's actually easy for someone

794
00:38:13,445 --> 00:38:15,486
to caricature or cosplay.

795
00:38:15,486 --> 00:38:16,607
I mean, break it down to like,

796
00:38:17,597 --> 00:38:20,301
we introduced this character, Diego Caplan, into Hogwarts.

797
00:38:20,301 --> 00:38:23,727
And he was designed with this bright yellow Hufflepuff scarf.

798
00:38:23,727 --> 00:38:26,312
And like, that's something you can draw.

799
00:38:26,312 --> 00:38:27,514
And the blue jean jacket.

800
00:38:27,514 --> 00:38:31,100
And sure enough, when people went to create fan art,

801
00:38:31,850 --> 00:38:33,290
This is a totally different art style.

802
00:38:33,290 --> 00:38:36,011
They're not trying to draw Diego Caplan in a way

803
00:38:36,011 --> 00:38:37,472
that you recognize him from the game.

804
00:38:37,472 --> 00:38:40,293
They've picked up on those visual elements.

805
00:38:40,293 --> 00:38:41,534
And that's what I'm talking about

806
00:38:41,534 --> 00:38:43,054
in terms of shareability.

807
00:38:43,054 --> 00:38:44,875
If you can do it in a few lines,

808
00:38:44,875 --> 00:38:48,037
it's more powerful because you've widened the audience

809
00:38:48,037 --> 00:38:51,078
of people who can then do fan art about your characters.

810
00:38:53,310 --> 00:38:58,092
Again, so for Marula Snyde, she's one of the main characters,

811
00:38:58,092 --> 00:38:59,712
she's got this highlight in her hair.

812
00:38:59,712 --> 00:39:00,893
And guess what?

813
00:39:00,893 --> 00:39:03,713
When people started to do fan art of Marula,

814
00:39:03,713 --> 00:39:05,054
that was the go-to element.

815
00:39:05,054 --> 00:39:06,654
Everybody picked up on it.

816
00:39:06,654 --> 00:39:09,515
Once you get that, you know who she is.

817
00:39:09,515 --> 00:39:11,016
And it transfers into real life too.

818
00:39:11,016 --> 00:39:13,216
So this young lady was doing the cosplay

819
00:39:13,216 --> 00:39:17,298
and she got the wig and did the bright highlight

820
00:39:17,298 --> 00:39:18,358
and boom, she's Marula.

821
00:39:18,358 --> 00:39:21,419
And that's the kind of thing that...

822
00:39:22,217 --> 00:39:28,680
lowers the barrier to entry for fans who might otherwise be like, I can't replicate this costume.

823
00:39:28,680 --> 00:39:33,442
Well, now you can. This is easy. This is simple and it's accessible and go out, do it, cosplay,

824
00:39:33,442 --> 00:39:41,945
and spread the love for Marula. And it's not just Harry Potter. I remember when we were

825
00:39:41,945 --> 00:39:46,347
at Telltale, we were talking to Gearbox about Tales from the Borderlands, and I asked them,

826
00:39:47,517 --> 00:39:48,938
about the relationship with the fans,

827
00:39:48,938 --> 00:39:49,998
and they were telling me that,

828
00:39:49,998 --> 00:39:52,459
even at the concept art stage,

829
00:39:52,459 --> 00:39:56,581
they think about their characters as being cosplay.

830
00:39:56,581 --> 00:39:59,422
Like, what body type is this good for cosplay?

831
00:39:59,422 --> 00:40:01,923
Or what visual element on this character

832
00:40:01,923 --> 00:40:03,224
is appropriate for cosplay?

833
00:40:03,224 --> 00:40:03,864
Can we simplify it?

834
00:40:03,864 --> 00:40:07,466
Can we heighten something so that people can do this,

835
00:40:07,466 --> 00:40:08,746
and that the fans can go out there

836
00:40:08,746 --> 00:40:10,847
and really celebrate the game,

837
00:40:10,847 --> 00:40:13,068
instead of making it so, I don't know,

838
00:40:13,068 --> 00:40:15,970
maybe visually complex that it's hard to cosplay?

839
00:40:16,190 --> 00:40:17,211
So you can see it right here.

840
00:40:17,211 --> 00:40:21,037
This is Maya, and she's got those three really strong

841
00:40:21,037 --> 00:40:24,341
visual elements, the hair, the yellow one piece, and this big

842
00:40:24,341 --> 00:40:24,942
old tattoo.

843
00:40:24,942 --> 00:40:30,630
And sure enough, someone goes out to cosplay, she nailed it.

844
00:40:30,630 --> 00:40:32,773
You would know who she was if you were even a casual fan of

845
00:40:32,773 --> 00:40:33,374
Borderlands.

846
00:40:34,841 --> 00:40:36,802
And you can also take it to the next level.

847
00:40:36,802 --> 00:40:39,343
Like this is not to exclude people

848
00:40:39,343 --> 00:40:41,705
who really want to go bananas on the costume.

849
00:40:41,705 --> 00:40:43,065
But you can see there's a range here

850
00:40:43,065 --> 00:40:45,947
and somewhat accessible range for people at the lower end

851
00:40:45,947 --> 00:40:48,448
who just like maybe are more casual fans.

852
00:40:48,448 --> 00:40:49,569
Well, now she's a cosplay fan.

853
00:40:49,569 --> 00:40:52,851
I don't actually know anything about this woman.

854
00:40:52,851 --> 00:40:54,411
She could be a totally dedicated cosplayer.

855
00:40:54,411 --> 00:40:59,094
But my point is creating something simple to replicate.

856
00:41:03,599 --> 00:41:09,283
Another thing is inclusive and representational characters and relationships inspire fans.

857
00:41:09,283 --> 00:41:14,407
So addressing and engaging underserved communities.

858
00:41:14,407 --> 00:41:16,489
We can do this.

859
00:41:16,489 --> 00:41:22,774
Like we just came up in Avengers Academy where there's a relationship between Niko and Carolina

860
00:41:22,774 --> 00:41:27,377
that's in the comics and they sort of have an on again off again thing.

861
00:41:29,113 --> 00:41:31,794
they wouldn't really touch this in the Avengers movie.

862
00:41:31,794 --> 00:41:33,676
You know, I think there's some media

863
00:41:33,676 --> 00:41:36,637
that feels it's too big to go for this type of thing.

864
00:41:36,637 --> 00:41:41,300
But we can work in the so-called margins of larger IP

865
00:41:41,300 --> 00:41:45,702
and create and address these communities

866
00:41:45,702 --> 00:41:49,665
and say like, look, you're part of this and draw them in.

867
00:41:49,665 --> 00:41:51,806
And that I got this off of a Tumblr

868
00:41:51,806 --> 00:41:54,147
because someone found it in the game and was so excited,

869
00:41:54,147 --> 00:41:55,748
they posted the whole sequence

870
00:41:55,748 --> 00:41:57,729
where Nico asked her out on a date.

871
00:41:58,554 --> 00:41:59,974
She says, I have a weird question.

872
00:41:59,974 --> 00:42:04,917
And it's just a really cute moment

873
00:42:04,917 --> 00:42:06,658
that we were able to put into the game.

874
00:42:06,658 --> 00:42:10,381
Someone saw it, felt like included, posted it,

875
00:42:10,381 --> 00:42:12,182
and then that went out to all their friends.

876
00:42:12,182 --> 00:42:15,384
And we saw it again with Walking Dead,

877
00:42:15,384 --> 00:42:18,065
where we introduced the possibility, the choice

878
00:42:18,065 --> 00:42:19,726
for a player to start a relationship,

879
00:42:19,726 --> 00:42:22,228
that Clementine and Violet could have a relationship.

880
00:42:22,228 --> 00:42:24,609
And we put this scene in where they have their first kiss.

881
00:42:25,365 --> 00:42:27,486
And of course, the community picked up on it.

882
00:42:27,486 --> 00:42:28,927
Immediately, the fan art started coming.

883
00:42:28,927 --> 00:42:30,828
And they really ran with it,

884
00:42:30,828 --> 00:42:32,709
to the point where they even created

885
00:42:32,709 --> 00:42:34,910
their own name for it.

886
00:42:34,910 --> 00:42:37,932
So, these communities,

887
00:42:37,932 --> 00:42:41,034
especially if they haven't been well-represented in the past

888
00:42:41,034 --> 00:42:42,855
can be extremely passionate

889
00:42:42,855 --> 00:42:45,776
if you represent them in your games and address them.

890
00:42:49,088 --> 00:42:51,610
Encouraging community response is key.

891
00:42:51,610 --> 00:42:54,211
And we do have a place in, you know,

892
00:42:54,211 --> 00:42:56,673
Hogwarts Mystery has a Facebook page,

893
00:42:56,673 --> 00:42:58,955
and occasionally they ask fun questions for the fans,

894
00:42:58,955 --> 00:43:00,996
like, what do you think of Diego?

895
00:43:00,996 --> 00:43:02,457
And people just love to pop off.

896
00:43:02,457 --> 00:43:04,919
And they just wanna have that outlet to say,

897
00:43:06,233 --> 00:43:07,594
you know, got a crush on this character,

898
00:43:07,594 --> 00:43:09,915
or no way, he's totally not my crush.

899
00:43:09,915 --> 00:43:12,276
Like, they want to sound off,

900
00:43:12,276 --> 00:43:15,198
and you should give them the space to do that.

901
00:43:15,198 --> 00:43:17,339
Not only is it just fun for the fans,

902
00:43:17,339 --> 00:43:20,100
but we look at these responses,

903
00:43:20,100 --> 00:43:21,161
and we think about, well,

904
00:43:21,161 --> 00:43:24,363
how do we include Diego in future episodes?

905
00:43:24,363 --> 00:43:24,963
How should we use him?

906
00:43:24,963 --> 00:43:26,084
How are people feeling about him?

907
00:43:26,084 --> 00:43:29,285
Even if sometimes it's negative.

908
00:43:29,285 --> 00:43:30,326
They're like, well, we don't like him,

909
00:43:30,326 --> 00:43:32,207
so then our job is to say,

910
00:43:32,207 --> 00:43:33,988
oh, we should probably make Diego more likable.

911
00:43:33,988 --> 00:43:34,748
What's wrong with him?

912
00:43:35,409 --> 00:43:43,598
And starting with that fan response, again, it's that circle. It informs new content.

913
00:43:43,598 --> 00:43:49,465
So finally, as a sort of a cap on this, don't explain your story to death. I know it's...

914
00:43:50,476 --> 00:43:52,717
We all get very passionate about the stories we want to tell,

915
00:43:52,717 --> 00:43:54,638
but I've found over and over again,

916
00:43:54,638 --> 00:43:57,500
it's actually really important to leave space.

917
00:43:57,500 --> 00:43:59,521
Don't say everything you think you need to say.

918
00:43:59,521 --> 00:44:02,342
Because the fans need to have space.

919
00:44:02,342 --> 00:44:06,105
They need to have a void that they can fill

920
00:44:06,105 --> 00:44:08,266
with their enthusiasm and with their imagination.

921
00:44:08,266 --> 00:44:11,507
Because they can't imagine any more about your characters

922
00:44:11,507 --> 00:44:13,609
because you've said literally everything.

923
00:44:14,609 --> 00:44:17,572
Again, that's not the circle, that's information.

924
00:44:17,572 --> 00:44:22,297
You're downloading data and they're not robots and you're not robots.

925
00:44:22,297 --> 00:44:23,118
And especially shippers.

926
00:44:23,118 --> 00:44:23,438
Shippers will...

927
00:44:23,438 --> 00:44:28,744
If you have two characters who have any kind of sexual chemistry, don't be tempted to have

928
00:44:28,744 --> 00:44:30,866
them kiss and have a relationship.

929
00:44:30,866 --> 00:44:33,409
You will get so much more mileage out of a wink or a look.

930
00:44:33,409 --> 00:44:34,150
I guarantee it.

931
00:44:35,465 --> 00:44:38,187
And give people space to tell their own stories.

932
00:44:38,187 --> 00:44:39,387
Could be on forums.

933
00:44:39,387 --> 00:44:42,509
You know, fan fiction is really powerful.

934
00:44:42,509 --> 00:44:44,871
But give these communities a place to talk.

935
00:44:44,871 --> 00:44:47,113
Because remember, you can tell one story.

936
00:44:47,113 --> 00:44:50,755
You have time to tell one story, then you ship it.

937
00:44:50,755 --> 00:44:52,756
But they can tell a million.

938
00:44:52,756 --> 00:44:54,538
And let them tell a million.

939
00:44:54,538 --> 00:44:57,059
Build your stories to be accessible in that way.

940
00:44:58,088 --> 00:44:59,589
And I found this really cool graphic.

