00:46:25,025 --> 00:46:29,707
where you know you have to be serving some sort of premium economical sort of

965
00:46:29,707 --> 00:46:34,950
aspect through your choices and how do you balance making sure that both choices feel appropriate

966
00:46:34,950 --> 00:46:38,892
but for the character and that players don't feel like they're being funneled away from

967
00:46:38,892 --> 00:46:41,554
something because they can't necessarily afford the energy at that time? Yeah, I mean that is

968
00:46:41,554 --> 00:46:46,516
the tough question, right? How to do that? I think we're figuring it all out and there's

969
00:46:46,516 --> 00:46:52,179
a couple of different modes. Choices sort of has an aesthetic where

970
00:46:54,386 --> 00:46:59,030
you kind of buy up front as opposed to along the way.

971
00:46:59,030 --> 00:47:02,192
And I think that is easier to handle narratively,

972
00:47:02,192 --> 00:47:03,153
like as a chunk.

973
00:47:03,153 --> 00:47:06,856
I think we're used to consuming media in chunks,

974
00:47:06,856 --> 00:47:11,920
whether it's a book or a movie or something like that,

975
00:47:11,920 --> 00:47:16,744
where that payment is more for unlocking a content.

976
00:47:19,000 --> 00:47:24,002
And formats where you sort of are interrupted

977
00:47:24,002 --> 00:47:26,003
with a sudden choice that comes out of nowhere

978
00:47:26,003 --> 00:47:27,243
and it's a monetization choice,

979
00:47:27,243 --> 00:47:30,084
you didn't see it coming, can feel really abrupt.

980
00:47:30,084 --> 00:47:31,665
Now, obviously, they're still profitable.

981
00:47:31,665 --> 00:47:33,406
I'm not saying it doesn't work.

982
00:47:33,406 --> 00:47:35,286
I'm just, I'm wary of those

